{ Once again, seizing space and keeping lines closed. Now  4...Bg7  5.Nc3  transposes to @@StartFEN@@rnbqkb1r/pppppp1p/5np1/8/2PP3P/8/PP2PPP1/RNBQKBNR b KQkq - 0 3@@EndFEN@@  3...Bg7  4.Nc3  c5  5.d5  and @@StartFEN@@rnbqkb1r/pp1ppp1p/5np1/2pP4/2P4P/8/PP2PPP1/RNBQKBNR b KQkq - 0 4@@EndFEN@@  4...d6  usually also leads to a transposition after a subsequent ...Bg7. }
