1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 g6 3. h4 d5
{ This might well be the choice of a Grünfeldeer at club level, but is also a move that White should relish appearing on the board. }
4. cxd5
{ There is absolutely no reason not to capture, especially when after  4...Nxd5  and a subsequent  5.e4  Black won't find a knight on c3 to exchange off and will be forced to retreat from d5. }
