12. d5 Nb4 13. Rb1
{ White drives back the knight, can always also go a2-a3 if needed, is ready to corral the knight with Bd2 should it dare to take on a2, and refuses to fear the check: }
13... Nc2+ 14. Kd2 Nd4 15. Bb2 Bg7 16. Ne2
{ The pin doesn't quite win a piece, but it's not hard to appreciate that White will be doing very well thanks to Harry once he's taken on g7 then g5. }
