{ Just like in the main lines of the Grünfeld. Compared to  8...Bg7  @@StartBracket@@when  9.f4!  is extremely likely to transpose after  9...c5  @@EndBracket@@, @@StartFEN@@rnbqkb1r/ppp1pp2/7p/6pP/3PP3/2P5/P4PP1/R1BQKBNR b KQkq - 0 8@@EndFEN@@  8...c5  allows White some extra options, not least  9.Bb5+!?  , but he can also be bold and strike out on the kingside: }
