13... Nxd4 14. Rb1
{ There's no need for White to fear any check on c2 @@StartBracket@@the king will be quite safe on f2@@EndBracket@@, and we already quite like his game. The rook on b1 is clearly well placed now away from the long diagonal and Harry is set to have a major role to play, whether White gets to make him passed with an exchange on h6 or if Black goes in for ...hxg5; Bxg5. }
