Bxc4 O-O
{ This was the course of Jacobsen-D.Andersen, Hillerod 2020, where we can't really explain why White didn't advance: }
8. e5
{ Blunting the fianchettoed bishop and ensuring White of a pleasant advantage. The bishop can always drop back from g5 to f4 and after Qd2 and O-O-O White might well look to attack on the kingside, with both Bh6 and a disruptive pawn sacrifice in the shape of e5-e6 very much ideas to bear in mind. }
