{ A switch to simple development. Black is a pawn up, but his position is pretty unpleasant due to his lack of dark-square control. Indeed, White might simply go O-O, Bf4 @@StartBracket@@or Be3 – Bh6 if ...O-O – and f2-f4@@EndBracket@@, e4-e5 and roll forwards, with a powerful initiative. }
