[White "1. Grünfeldesque Lines (...d5)"]
[Black "1C | Grünfeld with 3...h5 + 4...d5 | Black plays 5...Bg7, 6...c6, 8...Nxc3"]
[Result "*"]

1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 g6 3. h4 h5
{ Black elects to keep the h-file closed ahead of instigating a Grünfeld-type counter in the centre. }
4. Nc3
{ White prepares to expand with e2-e4 and now Black doesn't have to head for King's Indian waters, as we'll consider in Chapter Two, but might strike out with arguably the best version of a Grünfeld that we'll see in this chapter. }
