bxc3 cxd5 10. Bd3
{ White enjoys a pleasant edge. His queen's rook will enjoy a decent view from b1, the king can go to g1 and either c3-c4 or e3-e4 should lead to Black coming under some pressure, not least against e7. And what about a certain pin? }
10... Bg4 11. Qb3
{ White calmly gets out of the pin, refuses to fear doubled pawns @@StartBracket@@they would but increase the central control@@EndBracket@@, and threatens to pick off b7 then d5. }
