{ Black is extremely likely to castle, thereby meaning that he can recapture on d8 with his rook in the event of any ...e5; dxe5 dxe5 exchange. }
7. Nf3
{ Continuing to follow the Classical main line of the King's Indian, but, worry not, White won't be castling short next move. }
7... Bg4 8. Be3
{ Black's bishop development makes some sense with White no longer able to go h3, but the downside is that the dark-squared bishop can safely settle on e3.  White is now set to retain control and complete development with Qc2, O-O and Rad1, although ideas of Qd2 and O-O-O are by no means ridiculous either, and neither is a timely Ng5 leap. }
8... Nbd7
{ A surprisingly common choice here. It does complete development but might also leave Black slightly passively placed.   8...e5  9.d5  a5  was seen in Trent-Yordanov, Internet  (blitz)  2021, where  10.Nd2  was a good positional choice and our favourite leap would be another:  10.Ng5!   Now if Black retreats White will simply lumber up with Qd2,  O-O-O,  f2-f3 and Rdg1 if needed. However, exchanging the bishops instead tends to be a positional error in the King's Indian as it rather weakens Black's light squares:   10...Bxe2  11.Qxe2  . With ...f5 always now set to be met by Ne6,  White might even simply castle short, but f2-f3 @@StartBracket@@after Bd2 if  11...Ng4  @@EndBracket@@, O-O-O and then g2-g4 is the aggressive plan he'd prefer to deploy. }
9. Qc2
{ White is once again ready to meet any ...c5 with d4-d5, relying on his space advantage to help deny Black sufficient counterplay. Furthermore, the d1-square is freed up for a rook. }
9... c6 10. Rd1
{ Ruling out ...e5 for now and also allowing White to consider that advance himself. }
10... a6 11. e5 { A tempting if bold advance. } 11... Ne8 12. Ng5
{ The key follow-up as White prepares to sacrifice e5 for the initiative. }
12... Bxe2 13. Nxe2
{ Maintaining control, although even  13.Kxe2  is possible and if  13...dxe5  14.dxe5  Bxe5  when  15.g4!?  and even  15.Ne6!?  are options. }
13... dxe5 14. dxe5 Bxe5 15. f4
{ With f4-f5 imminent, as well as simply O-O and Nd4, White enjoyed a space advantage, the initiative and promising compensation in Mozelius-Ruiz Jarabo, correspondence 2017. }
