{ Once again, we see White keen not to fall too far behind in development while preparing e2-e4. }
4... d6
{ We'll take this as our main line, in part just because it's been by far Black's most popular move. }
5. e4 { Needless to say, White expands without delay. } 5... Na6 6. Be2
{ Sensibly not looking to punish the slightly unexpected arrival of the knight on the rim and now the logical  6...e5  7.d5  Nc5  8.Qc2  would transpose to our coverage of 5...Nbd7. }
