8... e6 9. f4
{ Needless to say, this is an extremely tempting advance with Black unable to invade on g4. }
9... Ned7 10. dxe6
{ Breaking up the black kingside as White goes straight for the attack. } 10...
fxe6 11. hxg6 hxg6 12. Be3
{ Calm development, if by no means the only tempting option, with  12.Nf3  Nc5  13.Ng5  preferred in Fedoseev-Zhuravleva, Internet @@StartBracket@@blitz@@EndBracket@@ 2019.  The text move prepares to meet @@StartFEN@@r1bq1rk1/pppn2b1/3ppnp1/8/2P1PP2/2N1B3/PP2B1P1/R2QK1NR b KQ - 1 12@@EndFEN@@  12...Nc5  with  13.e5  and Qc2,  and in any case White just has a very strong attack brewing: }
12... e5 13. f5
{ Already we can comfortably state that Black will have a hard time surviving on the kingside with g2-g4 imminent, as well as ideas of Nh3-g5. }
